The '''short-billed honeycreeper''' ('''''Cyanerpes nitidus''''') is a species of [[bird]] in the family [[Thraupidae]]. It is found in [[Bolivia]], [[Brazil]], [[Colombia]], [[Ecuador]], [[Peru]], [[Suriname]], and [[Venezuela]]. Its natural [[habitat]] is [[subtropical]] or [[tropical]] moist lowland [[forest]]s.

